AttributeList.Text: Written BY Kristopher Gimenez January 26,2023 This block is used to control TD auxilarry functions
When PTO is pressed there will be a 5 seconds pulse allowing operations.
Turn on Hot Oil Shuttle in Make up or Break Out if not Bypass Start

MaintContirm - PTO must be pressed before Quill Lock Switch Engage and rotary stopped- Set/Reset Maint Hold Close Time set if TD Mode Sw is used while Auto Closing. Reset if not Auto Closing an all Sw off.
Auto open if Break out finished or Makeup sw released
Used to catch the torq above setpoint
Used to disabled Quill Lock if BO was last function performed. MU cycle must be completed to enable.
Allow Maintain Close if Not Auto Open - Quill Lock Enabled
Close BUW if Auto Close, or Hold Closed, or Maintain Close and Quill lock and Interlock, or Quill Lock and Bypass start or bypass running
Clock is on for 5 seconds a minute when Not BUW Cl, not Quill lock, not gripper close and throttle>zero
Gripper Open coil will activate for 2 mins when Not Closing BUW. It will then periodically turn on for 5 seconds every minute while throttle is above zero
While SW held in close position hold output on for 10 s if no feedback, or hold for close position for 5s with feedback =1 (on)
Open elevators if Elev Op, Not Elev CL, PTO Confirmed, not bypass start , not bypass running. Allow Elev to be on for 8 seconds to open. Note PTO must be confirmed before Open signal received.
Disable Links if In make up spin and PTO pressed. Link tilt input used as speed control in Make Up Spin
Do not allow the MSV to close if Pump is running, allow 5 seconds from drop of pumps running signal before allowing close. In Auto mode open when pump runnign and close after delay
Unloader is valve is on if Drill throttle greater than zero and no Auxiliary functions are being used
